README

This project was created for a class course.

Prerrequisites:
===============
Watson:
-------
1. Create a IBM Cloud Account

2. Install Watson Developer Cloud
pip install -I watson-developer-cloud==0.26.1

For more reference:
https://console.bluemix.net/docs/services/discovery/getting-started.html#getting-started-with-the-api
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q4SVFg6bN5E&feature=youtu.be
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kwmqJRDbv98&feature=youtu.be

Google:
-------
1. Create an Account

2. Install google services


Run the program
=========================================
The project works as follows:
1. First you need to select an audio file
2. The file will be transcribed to text using google cloud services library
3. The text will be sent to Watson Cloud Services to query the data (already stored in a collection)
4. The text result will be transformed to Audio
5. The audio will be played

To start, run alfred.py file

This project contains several python files for Watson communication
